---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import DiagramPlaceholder from '../components/DiagramPlaceholder.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy" description="How Open Working Hours protects your data with privacy-by-design principles, k-anonymity, and GDPR compliance.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-gray-900 mb-4">Privacy &amp; Protection</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl">
        Privacy is not an afterthought. It's the foundation of how Open Working Hours is designed and operated.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Privacy by Design -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-gray-900 mb-6">Privacy by design</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>Data minimization:</strong> We collect only what's necessary for aggregation. No names, no precise locations, no employer identifiers.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>Pseudonymization:</strong> Users are identified by random tokens, not personal information. Email is only used for verification, then discarded from operational data.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>Encryption in transit:</strong> All communication between the app and our servers uses TLS 1.3. Data at rest is encrypted on the server.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>K-anonymity protection:</strong> Statistics are only published when at least 10 individuals contribute to a group. Small groups are suppressed entirely.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>User controls:</strong> Export all your data or delete your account at any time. Deletion is permanent and cascades to all associated records.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <strong>No employer access:</strong> This is not an employer tool. Your employer cannot see your data, cannot request access, and is not part of the system.
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Data Collected Table -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-gray-900 mb-6">What we collect</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-100 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-green-800 font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            Collected
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-900 text-sm">
            <li>Daily working hours (confirmed by you)</li>
            <li>Break duration</li>
            <li>Federal state (Bundesland)</li>
            <li>Medical specialty category</li>
            <li>Role level (e.g., resident, attending)</li>
            <li>Anonymous usage token</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-100 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-red-800 font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
            </svg>
            Not collected
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-900 text-sm">
            <li>Your name</li>
            <li>Hospital or employer name</li>
            <li>Precise location coordinates</li>
            <li>IP address (not stored)</li>
            <li>Device identifiers</li>
            <li>Contacts, calendar, or other app data</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Re-identification Protection -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-gray-900 mb-6">Protection against re-identification</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Even with anonymized data, small groups could potentially be identified. We implement multiple safeguards:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 ml-4">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gray-400">•</span>
          <span><strong>Minimum group size:</strong> Statistics require at least 10 contributors (k ≥ 10)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gray-400">•</span>
          <span><strong>Cell suppression:</strong> Groups below the threshold are completely hidden, not approximated</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-gray-400">•</span>
          <span><strong>Statistical noise:</strong> Aggregates include calibrated noise (Laplace mechanism, ε=1.0) to prevent inference attacks</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Diagram -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <DiagramPlaceholder
        label="Data Flow Diagram"
        description={`IMAGE GENERATION PROMPT — Privacy Architecture / Data Flow Diagram

STYLE:
Technical blueprint illustration. Light blue (#60A5FA) line art on subtle grid background (#E0F2FE). Clean, precise, minimal. Reference: 1Password security whitepaper diagrams, security architecture documentation. Flat technical drawing aesthetic with clear visual hierarchy.

COMPOSITION (three distinct layers/zones, left to right):

LAYER 1 — "YOUR DEVICE" (leftmost, light background):
- Smartphone icon with small database cylinder inside
- Lock/padlock symbol overlay
- Label: "Local Storage (encrypted)"
- Visual boundary: dashed rectangle enclosing this zone

LAYER 2 — "SECURE BACKEND" (center, slightly darker background):
- Server/cloud icon
- TWO separate data containers shown:
  a) "Raw Events" table icon with label "(pseudonymous)" — individual records
  b) "Aggregated Stats" table icon with label "(anonymous)" — grouped statistics
- Arrow connecting Raw Events → Aggregated Stats (internal processing)
- Shield icon indicating security
- Label at bottom: "Individual records stay here"

LAYER 3 — "PUBLIC DASHBOARD" (rightmost):
- Simple bar chart icon
- Label: "Aggregated Statistics Only"
- No lock symbol (data is public but anonymous)

ARROWS BETWEEN LAYERS:
- Layer 1 → Layer 2: Arrow labeled "TLS 1.3 encrypted"
- Layer 2 → Layer 3: Arrow labeled "k-anonymized (n≥10)"

KEY VISUAL CONCEPTS:
- Clear separation between private, processing, and public zones
- Individual data NEVER reaches Layer 3 (show this visually)
- Aggregation is the key transformation (many → few)
- Encryption protects data in transit
- Pseudonymous ≠ anonymous (different levels shown)

IMPORTANT ANNOTATION:
Include small text note: "Individual records never leave the backend"

DIMENSIONS: Wide format (16:7), suitable for full-width display.

COLOR CODING (optional):
- Layer 1: Lightest blue tint
- Layer 2: Medium blue tint
- Layer 3: White/neutral

DO NOT INCLUDE: Photographs, realistic people, red/warning colors, complex 3D, dark themes.`}
        aspectRatio="16/7"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Deletion and Export -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-gray-900 mb-6">Deletion &amp; export</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        GDPR grants you rights over your data. We make these easy to exercise:
      </p>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Export</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Download all your submitted data in JSON format from the app settings.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Deletion</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Delete your account from the app. All personal data and work events are permanently removed. Previously aggregated statistics (which contain no personal data) are retained.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Link to formal policy -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-8">
      <p class="text-gray-600">
        For the complete legal privacy policy, see our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">formal Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
